^New: Full Quest Campaign!
|10New: Full Quest Campaign!
|06-------------------------
|1014 new quests|02 have been added, bringing the total to |1020|02.  The quests
form a full campaign with branching paths, player choices, and a finale
that will test even the strongest clans.

|10How to start:|02  Talk to the villagers!  Many NPCs have stories to tell
and favours to ask.  Some quests are available right away, while others
unlock only after you have proven yourself.

|10Hints:|02
 |14*|02 Completing one quest often leads to the next.  Pay attention to
   what the NPCs tell you after you return victorious.
 |14*|02 A certain historian knows more than he lets on about ancient evils.
 |14*|02 The orcs are not the only threat lurking in these mines . . .
 |14*|02 The mightiest weapon in the game cannot be bought.  It must be
   earned.
^END

^What's New Since v0.93
|10What's new in v0.94 to v0.97b2
|06-------------------------------
|02The Clans has been modernized substantially since its original DOS/Windows
release:

- Ported to FreeBSD, Linux, and modern Windows (MinGW/MSVC); DOS-era
  dependencies such as SHARE.EXE removed
- Numerous bug fixes: memory leaks, buffer overflows, IBBS packet
  handling, serialization, and combat edge cases resolved
- Build system overhauled: GNUmakefile with automated dependencies,
  Visual Studio project files, and installer targets for Unix and Windows
- DevKit expanded: quest scripting test tool (qtest), improved langcomp
  and ecomp, and an integration test suite
- Help files corrected: stale references to removed mechanics (farms,
  approval/popularity, old command-line options) updated
- Dictatorship government type removed; democracy is now the only option
^END

^Coming Soon
|14Here are some features which may or may not appear in The Clans.  They
are being considered, however:|06

 * Roaming NPCs.  NPCs that travel from village to village (in a league)
 * Village Scenarios.  Sysop will choose from a list of village scenarios
   such as a port town, prairie village, etc.  Each type of village will
   have some unique races and classes and other options.  This will help
   vary villages from BBS to BBS in leagues.
 * If a user is online and someone tries to play, the waiting party may
   play a really cheap game and also be able to send a message to the
   person that is in the game playing.
 * New races, classes, and equipment.
^END
